  "question": "Relational Database",
  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n<title>Relational Database Interactive Exploration</title>\n<style>\n  body {\n    font-family: monospace, monospace;\n    background: white;\n    color: black;\n    margin: 10px;\n    line-height: 1.4;\n  }\n  input[type=text], select, textarea {\n    font-family: monospace, monospace;\n    font-size: 1em;\n    width: 100%;\n    box-sizing: border-box;\n  }\n  table {\n    border-collapse: collapse;\n    margin-top: 5px;\n    margin-bottom: 5px;\n    width: 100%;\n  }\n  table, th, td {\n    border: 1px solid black;\n    padding: 2px 4px;\n  }\n  button {\n    font-family: monospace, monospace;\n    font-size: 1em;\n  }\n  #state {\n    white-space: pre-wrap;\n    font-size: 0.9em;\n    border: 1px solid black;\n    padding: 3px;\n    margin-top: 5px;\n    max-height: 150px;\n    overflow-y: auto;\n    background: #f9f9f9;\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<h1>Relational Database Interactive Exploration</h1>\n\n<p>This tool demonstrates relational database concepts by letting you create tables, define columns with types, add rows, create relations (foreign keys), and perform basic queries / joins interactively.</p>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h2>1. Create or Manage Tables</h2>\n<div>\n  <label for=\"newTableName\">New Table Name: </label>\n  <input type=\"text\" id=\"newTableName\" placeholder=\"e.g. Employees\" />\n  <button id=\"btnCreateTable\">Create Table</button>\n  <button id=\"btnDropTable\">Drop Table</button>\n  <br /><br />\n  <label for=\"selectTable\">Select Table: </label>\n  <select id=\"selectTable\" style=\"min-width: 150px;\"></select>\n  <button id=\"btnLoadTable\">Load Table</button>\n  <button id=\"btnClearTableView\">Clear View</button>\n</div>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h2>2. Define / Edit Columns of Selected Table</h2>\n<div id=\"columnsSection\" style=\"display:none;\">\n  <p>\n    <label for=\"newColumnName\">Column Name: </label>\n    <input type=\"text\" id=\"newColumnName\" placeholder=\"e.g. ID\" style=\"width:120px;\" />\n    <label for=\"newColumnType\">Type: </label>\n    <select id=\"newColumnType\">\n      <option value=\"int\">int</option>\n      <option value=\"text\">text</option>\n      <option value=\"fk\">foreign key (relation)</option>\n    </select>\n    <span id=\"fkTargetTableContainer\" style=\"display:none;\">\n      <label for=\"fkTargetTable\">Target Table: </label>\n      <select id=\"fkTargetTable\"></select>\n      <label for=\"fkTargetColumn\">Target Column: </label>\n      <select id=\"fkTargetColumn\"></select>\n    </span>\n    <button id=\"btnAddColumn\">Add Column</button>\n  </p>\n  <div>\n    <strong>Columns in Table:</strong>\n    <table id=\"columnsTable\">\n      <thead><tr><th>Name</th><th>Type</th><th>FK Target</th><th>Actions</th></tr></thead>\n      <tbody></tbody>\n    </table>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h2>3. Add / Edit Rows in Selected Table</h2>\n<div id=\"rowsSection\" style=\"display:none;\">\n  <div id=\"rowInputForm\"></div>\n  <button id=\"btnAddRow\">Add Row</button>\n  <button id=\"btnClearRowInputs\">Clear Inputs</button>\n  <p><strong>Existing Rows:</strong></p>\n  <table id=\"rowsTable\">\n    <thead><tr id=\"rowsTableHeader\"></tr></thead>\n    <tbody></tbody>\n  </table>\n</div>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h2>4. Create / Manage Relations (FK Constraints)</h2>\n<div id=\"relationsSection\" style=\"display:none;\">\n  <p>\n    <label for=\"relSourceTable\">Source Table: </label>\n    <select id=\"relSourceTable\"></select>\n    <label for=\"relSourceColumn\">Source Column: </label>\n    <select id=\"relSourceColumn\"></select>\n    <label for=\"relTargetTable\">Target Table: </label>\n    <select id=\"relTargetTable\"></select>\n    <label for=\"relTargetColumn\">Target Column: </label>\n    <select id=\"relTargetColumn\"></select>\n    <button id=\"btnAddRelation\">Add Relation</button>\n  </p>\n  <div>\n    <strong>Current Relations (Foreign Keys):</strong>\n    <table id=\"relationsTable\">\n      <thead><tr><th>Source Table.Column</th><th>Target Table.Column</th><th>Actions</th></tr></thead>\n      <tbody></tbody>\n    </table>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h2>5. Query / Explore Data</h2>\n<div>\n  <p>Use this panel to formulate simple SELECT queries using interactive join controls.</p>\n  <div>\n    <label for=\"querySelectTables\">Tables (comma separated): </label>\n    <input type=\"text\" id=\"querySelectTables\" placeholder=\"e.g. Employees,Departments\" />\n  </div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:4px;\">\n    <label for=\"queryColumns\">Select Columns (comma separated, with optional table prefix): </label><br />\n    <input type=\"text\" id=\"queryColumns\" placeholder=\"e.g. Employees.Name,Departments.Name\" style=\"width:100%;\" />\n  </div>\n  <div style=\"margin-top:4px;\">\n    <label for=\"queryWhere\">WHERE Clause (simple conditions, e.g. Employees.Age &gt; 30): </label><br />\n    <input type=\"text\" id=\"queryWhere\" placeholder=\"e.g. Employees.Age > 30 AND Departments.Name = 'HR'\" style=\"width:100%;\" />\n  </div>\n  <button id=\"btnRunQuery\" style=\"margin-top:6px;\">Run Query</button>\n</div>\n\n<div id=\"queryResults\" style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n  <strong>Query Result:</strong>\n  <table id=\"queryResultTable\"><thead></thead><tbody></tbody></table>\n</div>\n\n<hr />\n\n<h2>Debug / State</h2>\n<pre id=\"state\" aria-live=\"polite\"></pre>\n\n<script>\n(() => {\n  // DATA MODEL\n  // Each table has name: string\n  // Each table has columns: [{name, type('int'|'text'|'fk'), fkTarget:{table,column} or null}]\n  // Each table has rows: array of objects with keys as column names\n  // Relations stored redundantly in columns with fkTarget set, and in relations array (for convenience)\n\n  // State object\n  const state = {\n    tables: {},\n    relations: [], // { sourceTable, sourceColumn, targetTable, targetColumn }\n  };\n\n  // Utility - Escape HTML for safety\n  function htmlEscape(str) {\n    if (typeof str !== 'string') return str;\n    return str.replace(/&/g,\"&amp;\").replace(/</g,\"&lt;\").replace(/>/g,\"&gt;\").replace(/\"/g,\"&quot;\");\n  }\n\n  // UI elements references\n  const newTableNameInput = document.getElementById('newTableName');\n  const btnCreateTable = document.getElementById('btnCreateTable');\n  const btnDropTable = document.getElementById('btnDropTable');\n  const selectTable = document.getElementById('selectTable');\n  const btnLoadTable = document.getElementById('btnLoadTable');\n  const btnClearTableView = document.getElementById('btnClearTableView');\n\n  const columnsSection = document.getElementById('columnsSection');\n  const newColumnNameInput = document.getElementById('newColumnName');\n  const newColumnTypeSelect = document.getElementById('newColumnType');\n  const fkTargetTableContainer = document.getElementById('fkTargetTableContainer');\n  const fkTargetTableSelect = document.getElementById('fkTargetTable');\n  const fkTargetColumnSelect = document.getElementById('fkTargetColumn');\n  const btnAddColumn = document.getElementById('btnAddColumn');\n  const columnsTableBody = document.querySelector('#columnsTable tbody');\n\n  const rowsSection = document.getElementById('rowsSection');\n  const rowInputForm = document.getElementById('rowInputForm');\n  const btnAddRow = document.getElementById('btnAddRow');\n  const btnClearRowInputs = document.getElementById('btnClearRowInputs');\n  const rowsTable = document.getElementById('rowsTable');\n  const rowsTableHeader = document.getElementById('rowsTableHeader');\n  const rowsTableBody = rowsTable.querySelector('tbody');\n\n  const relationsSection = document.getElementById('relationsSection');\n  const relSourceTableSelect = document.getElementById('relSourceTable');\n  const relSourceColumnSelect = document.getElementById('relSourceColumn');\n  const relTargetTableSelect = document.getElementById('relTargetTable');\n  const relTargetColumnSelect = document.getElementById('relTargetColumn');\n  const btnAddRelation = document.getElementById('btnAddRelation');\n  const relationsTableBody = document.querySelector('#relationsTable tbody');\n\n  const querySelectTablesInput = document.getElementById('querySelectTables');\n  const queryColumnsInput = document.getElementById('queryColumns');\n  const queryWhereInput = document.getElementById('queryWhere');\n  const btnRunQuery = document.getElementById('btnRunQuery');\n  const queryResultTable = document.getElementById('queryResultTable');\n  const queryResultThead = queryResultTable.querySelector('thead');\n  const queryResultTbody = queryResultTable.querySelector('tbody');\n\n  const statePre = document.getElementById('state');\n\n  // Display State for debugging\n  function updateStateView() {\n    statePre.textContent = JSON.stringify(state, null, 2);\n  }\n\n  // Update Select Table dropdown\n  function updateTablesDropdowns() {\n    // For selectTable + fkTargetTable + relation selects\n    const tables = Object.keys(state.tables).sort();\n    // Update selectTable\n    fillSelectOptions(selectTable, tables, null, \"(Select a table)\");\n    // fkTargetTable\n    fillSelectOptions(fkTargetTableSelect, tables);\n    updateFkTargetColumns();\n    // relations selects\n    fillSelectOptions(relSourceTableSelect, tables);\n    fillSelectOptions(relTargetTableSelect, tables);\n    updateRelSourceColumns();\n    updateRelTargetColumns();\n  }\n\n  function fillSelectOptions(selectElem, options, selectedValue = null, placeholder=null) {\n    selectElem.innerHTML = '';\n    if(placeholder) {\n      const opt = document.createElement('option');\n      opt.value = '';\n      opt.textContent = placeholder;\n      opt.disabled = true;\n      opt.selected = true;\n      selectElem.appendChild(opt);\n    }\n    options.forEach(o=>{\n      const opt = document.createElement('option');\n      opt.value = o;\n      opt.textContent = o;\n      if(selectedValue !== null && selectedValue === o) opt.selected = true;\n      selectElem.appendChild(opt);\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Load a table's columns and rows into UI\n  let currentTable = null;\n  function loadTable(name) {\n    if (!name || !state.tables[name]) {\n      alert(\"Invalid table selected.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    currentTable = name;\n    // Show column section\n    columnsSection.style.display = '';\n    rowsSection.style.display = '';\n    relationsSection.style.display = '';\n\n    // Load columns in UI\n    renderColumnsTable();\n\n    // Render row inputs\n    renderRowInputForm();\n\n    // Render rows table\n    renderRowsTable();\n\n    updateRelationsSection();\n\n  }\n\n  // Clear current view\n  function clearCurrentView() {\n    currentTable = null;\n    columnsSection.style.display = 'none';\n    rowsSection.style.display = 'none';\n    relationsSection.style.display = 'none';\n    columnsTableBody.innerHTML = '';\n    rowInputForm.innerHTML = '';\n    rowsTableHeader.innerHTML = '';\n    rowsTableBody.innerHTML = '';\n    relationsTableBody.innerHTML = '';\n  }\n\n  // Render columns table for currentTable\n  function renderColumnsTable() {\n    columnsTableBody.innerHTML = '';\n    if (!currentTable) return;\n    const cols = state.tables[currentTable].columns;\n    cols.forEach((col,i)=>{\n      const tr = document.createElement('tr');\n      const tdName = document.createElement('td');\n      tdName.textContent = col.name;\n      const tdType = document.createElement('td');\n      tdType.textContent = col.type;\n      const tdFk = document.createElement('td');\n      tdFk.textContent = '';\n      if(col.type === 'fk' && col.fkTarget) {\n        tdFk.textContent = col.fkTarget.table + '.' + col.fkTarget.column;\n      }\n      const tdActions = document.createElement('td');\n      const btnDel = document.createElement('button');\n      btnDel.textContent = 'Delete';\n      btnDel.onclick = () => {\n        if(confirm(`Delete column \"${col.name}\" from table \"${currentTable}\"? This will remove data from rows.`)) {\n          deleteColumn(currentTable, col.name);\n        }\n      };\n      tdActions.appendChild(btnDel);\n      tr.appendChild(tdName);\n      tr.appendChild(tdType);\n      tr.appendChild(tdFk);\n      tr.appendChild(tdActions);\n      columnsTableBody.appendChild(tr);\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Delete column from table\n  function deleteColumn(table, colName) {\n    const t = state.tables[table];\n    if(!t) return;\n    // Remove column from columns\n    const idx = t.columns.findIndex(c => c.name === colName);\n    if(idx < 0) return;\n    // Remove any relations involving this column\n    state.relations = state.relations.filter(rel => !( (rel.sourceTable === table && rel.sourceColumn === colName) || (rel.targetTable === table && rel.targetColumn === colName) ));\n    // Remove column\n    t.columns.splice(idx,1);\n    // Remove from rows\n    t.rows.forEach(r=>{\n      delete r[colName];\n    });\n    renderColumnsTable();\n    renderRowsTable();\n    updateRelationsSection();\n    updateStateView();\n    updateTablesDropdowns();\n  }\n\n  // Render row input form for currentTable\n  function renderRowInputForm() {\n    if(!currentTable) {\n      rowInputForm.innerHTML = '';\n      return;\n    }\n    const cols = state.tables[currentTable].columns;\n    rowInputForm.innerHTML = '';\n    cols.forEach(col=>{\n      const div = document.createElement('div');\n      div.style.marginBottom = '4px';\n\n      const lbl = document.createElement('label');\n      lbl.textContent = col.name + ' (' + col.type + '): ';\n      lbl.htmlFor = 'rowinput-'+col.name;\n      div.appendChild(lbl);\n\n      if(col.type === 'fk' && col.fkTarget) {\n        // input select - values from target table\n        const sel = document.createElement('select');\n        sel.id = 'rowinput-'+col.name;\n        // Add empty option\n        const emptyOpt = document.createElement('option');\n        emptyOpt.value = '';\n        emptyOpt.textContent = '(null)';\n        sel.appendChild(emptyOpt);\n        const targetTable = state.tables[col.fkTarget.table];\n        if(targetTable) {\n          const targetCol = col.fkTarget.column;\n          targetTable.rows.forEach(r => {\n            const val = r[targetCol];\n            const opt = document.createElement('option');\n            opt.value = val === undefined || val === null ? '' : String(val);\n            opt.textContent = String(val);\n            sel.appendChild(opt);\n          });\n        }\n        div.appendChild(sel);\n      } else {\n        const input = document.createElement('input');\n        input.type = 'text';\n        input.id = 'rowinput-'+col.name;\n        input.placeholder = col.type === 'int' ? 'integer' : 'text';\n        div.appendChild(input);\n      }\n      rowInputForm.appendChild(div);\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Render rows table for currentTable\n  function renderRowsTable() {\n    if(!currentTable) {\n      rowsTableHeader.innerHTML = '';\n      rowsTableBody.innerHTML = '';\n      return;\n    }\n    const t = state.tables[currentTable];\n    const cols = t.columns;\n    rowsTableHeader.innerHTML = '';\n    rowsTableBody.innerHTML = '';\n    // Table header\n    cols.forEach(col=>{\n      const th = document.createElement('th');\n      th.textContent = col.name;\n      rowsTableHeader.appendChild(th);\n    });\n    const thActions = document.createElement('th');\n    thActions.textContent = 'Actions';\n    rowsTableHeader.appendChild(thActions);\n\n    // Rows body\n    t.rows.forEach((r,i)=>{\n      const tr = document.createElement('tr');\n      cols.forEach(col=>{\n        const td = document.createElement('td');\n        let val = r[col.name];\n        if(val === undefined || val === null) val = '';\n        td.textContent = String(val);\n        tr.appendChild(td);\n      });\n      const tdActions = document.createElement('td');\n      // Edit button\n      const btnEdit = document.createElement('button');\n      btnEdit.textContent = 'Edit';\n      btnEdit.onclick = () => {\n        populateRowInputsForEdit(i);\n      };\n      // Delete button\n      const btnDel = document.createElement('button');\n      btnDel.textContent = 'Delete';\n      btnDel.onclick = () => {\n        if(confirm(`Delete row ${i+1} from table \"${currentTable}\"?`)) {\n          deleteRow(currentTable, i);\n        }\n      };\n      tdActions.appendChild(btnEdit);\n      tdActions.appendChild(document.createTextNode(' '));\n      tdActions.appendChild(btnDel);\n      tr.appendChild(tdActions);\n      rowsTableBody.appendChild(tr);\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Populate row input fields for edit mode\n  let editingRowIndex = null;\n  function populateRowInputsForEdit(rowIndex) {\n    if(!currentTable) return;\n    const row = state.tables[currentTable].rows[rowIndex];\n    if(!row) return;\n    editingRowIndex = rowIndex;\n    state.tables[currentTable].columns.forEach(col=>{\n      const el = document.getElementById('rowinput-'+col.name);\n      if(!el) return;\n      const val = row[col.name];\n      if(el.tagName === 'SELECT') {\n        // Set selected option by val\n        for(let i=0;i<el.options.length;i++) {\n          if(el.options[i].value === (val === undefined || val === null ? '' : String(val))) {\n            el.selectedIndex = i;\n            break;\n          }\n        }\n      } else {\n        el.value = val === undefined || val === null ? '' : String(val);\n      }\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Clear row inputs and cancel edit mode\n  function clearRowInputs() {\n    editingRowIndex = null;\n    state.tables[currentTable].columns.forEach(col=>{\n      const el = document.getElementById('rowinput-'+col.name);\n      if(!el) return;\n      if(el.tagName === 'SELECT') {\n        el.selectedIndex = 0;\n      } else {\n        el.value = '';\n      }\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Add or Update a row in currentTable\n  function addOrUpdateRow() {\n    if(!currentTable) return;\n    const t = state.tables[currentTable];\n    const newRow = {};\n    // Validate and collect inputs\n    for(const col of t.columns) {\n      const el = document.getElementById('rowinput-'+col.name);\n      if(!el) continue;\n      // Validate based on type\n      let valRaw = '';\n      if(el.tagName === 'SELECT') {\n        valRaw = el.value.trim();\n      } else {\n        valRaw = el.value.trim();\n      }\n      if(col.type === 'int') {\n        if(valRaw === '') {\n          newRow[col.name] = null;\n        } else {\n          const n = parseInt(valRaw,10);\n          if(isNaN(n)) {\n            alert(`Invalid integer value for column \"${col.name}\"`);\n            return;\n          }\n          newRow[col.name] = n;\n        }\n      } else if(col.type === 'text') {\n        newRow[col.name] = valRaw;\n      } else if(col.type === 'fk') {\n        newRow[col.name] = valRaw === '' ? null : valRaw;\n        // Validate FK referential integrity\n        if(valRaw !== '') {\n          if(!validateForeignKey(col.fkTarget.table, col.fkTarget.column, valRaw)) {\n            alert(`Foreign key constraint failed: value \"${valRaw}\" not found in ${col.fkTarget.table}.${col.fkTarget.column}`);\n            return;\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n    if(editingRowIndex !== null) {\n      // Update existing row\n      t.rows[editingRowIndex] = newRow;\n      editingRowIndex = null;\n    } else {\n      // Append new row\n      t.rows.push(newRow);\n    }\n    clearRowInputs();\n    renderRowsTable();\n    updateStateView();\n    updateFkTargetColumns();\n  }\n\n  // Delete row\n  function deleteRow(tableName, index) {\n    const t = state.tables[tableName];\n    if(!t) return;\n    if(index<0 || index>=t.rows.length) return;\n    // Check if row is referenced by any foreign key in other tables (referential integrity)\n    for(const rel of state.relations) {\n      if(rel.targetTable === tableName) {\n        // For each referencing row in sourceTable sourceColumn check if has FK value equal to the to-be-deleted\n        const valToCheck = t.rows[index][rel.targetColumn];\n        for(const rRow of state.tables[rel.sourceTable].rows) {\n          if(rRow[rel.sourceColumn] === valToCheck) {\n            alert(`Cannot delete row because it is referenced by foreign key in table \"${rel.sourceTable}\", column \"${rel.sourceColumn}\"`);\n            return;\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    t.rows.splice(index,1);\n    renderRowsTable();\n    updateStateView();\n    updateFkTargetColumns();\n  }\n\n  // Validate FK value exists in target table column\n  function validateForeignKey(targetTable, targetColumn, val) {\n    if(!state.tables[targetTable]) return false;\n    const rows = state.tables[targetTable].rows;\n    for(const r of rows) {\n      if(String(r[targetColumn]) === val) return true;\n    }\n    return false;\n  }\n\n  // When FK target table changes, update FK target column options to existing columns (int or text)\n  function updateFkTargetColumns() {\n    const tName = fkTargetTableSelect.value;\n    fkTargetColumnSelect.innerHTML = '';\n    if(!tName || !state.tables[tName]) return;\n    const cols = state.tables[tName].columns.filter(c=> c.type === 'int' || c.type === 'text');\n    cols.forEach(c=>{\n      const opt = document.createElement('option');\n      opt.value = c.name;\n      opt.textContent = c.name;\n      fkTargetColumnSelect.appendChild(opt);\n    });\n  }\n\n  fkTargetTableSelect.addEventListener('change', updateFkTargetColumns);\n\n  // Show or hide FK target table/column selectors depending on selected column type\n  newColumnTypeSelect.addEventListener('change', () => {\n    if(newColumnTypeSelect.value === 'fk') {\n      fkTargetTableContainer.style.display = '';\n      updateFkTargetColumns();\n    } else {\n      fkTargetTableContainer.style.display = 'none';\n    }\n  });\n\n  // Add column to currentTable when clicked\n  btnAddColumn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    if(!currentTable) {\n      alert('No table loaded.');\n      return;\n    }\n    const colName = newColumnNameInput.value.trim();\n    if(!colName) {\n      alert('Column name cannot be empty.');\n      return;\n    }\n    // Validate column name unique within table\n    if(state.tables[currentTable].columns.some(c=>c.name === colName)) {\n      alert(`Column \"${colName}\" already exists in table \"${currentTable}\".`);\n      return;\n    }\n    const colType = newColumnTypeSelect.value;\n    let fkTarget = null;\n    if(colType === 'fk') {\n      const tgtTable = fkTargetTableSelect.value;\n      const tgtColumn = fkTargetColumnSelect.value;\n      if(!tgtTable || !tgtColumn) {\n        alert('Foreign key target table and column must be selected.');\n        return;\n      }\n      fkTarget = {table: tgtTable, column: tgtColumn};\n    }\n    // Add column\n    state.tables[currentTable].columns.push({name: colName, type: colType, fkTarget: fkTarget});\n    // Add null default to existing rows for this column\n    state.tables[currentTable].rows.forEach(r=>{\n      r[colName] = null;\n    });\n    renderColumnsTable();\n    renderRowInputForm();\n    renderRowsTable();\n    updateStateView();\n    updateTablesDropdowns();\n\n    // Clear inputs\n    newColumnNameInput.value = '';\n  });\n\n  // Add row button event\n  btnAddRow.addEventListener('click', addOrUpdateRow);\n\n  // Clear row inputs button\n  btnClearRowInputs.addEventListener('click', clearRowInputs);\n\n  // Create a new table button\n  btnCreateTable.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    const tname = newTableNameInput.value.trim();\n    if(!tname) {\n      alert('Table name cannot be empty.');\n      return;\n    }\n    if(state.tables[tname]) {\n      alert(`Table \"${tname}\" already exists.`);\n      return;\n    }\n    state.tables[tname] = {columns: [], rows: []};\n    newTableNameInput.value = '';\n    updateTablesDropdowns();\n    updateStateView();\n  });\n\n  // Drop table button\n  btnDropTable.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    const tname = newTableNameInput.value.trim();\n    if(!tname || !state.tables[tname]) {\n      alert('Invalid table name to drop.');\n      return;\n    }\n    // Check if table is referenced by any FK relations\n    for(const rel of state.relations) {\n      if(rel.targetTable === tname || rel.sourceTable === tname) {\n        alert(`Cannot drop table \"${tname}\" because it is involved in foreign key relations.`);\n        return;\n      }\n    }\n    if(confirm(`Are you sure to drop table \"${tname}\"? This operation cannot be undone.`)) {\n      delete state.tables[tname];\n      updateTablesDropdowns();\n      updateStateView();\n      if(currentTable === tname) clearCurrentView();\n    }\n  });\n\n  btnLoadTable.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    const tname = selectTable.value;\n    if(!tname) {\n      alert('No table selected.');\n      return;\n    }\n    loadTable(tname);\n  });\n\n  btnClearTableView.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    clearCurrentView();\n  });\n\n  // RELATIONS SECTION controls\n\n  function updateRelSourceColumns() {\n    const tname = relSourceTableSelect.value;\n    relSourceColumnSelect.innerHTML = '';\n    if(!tname || !state.tables[tname]) return;\n    const cols = state.tables[tname].columns;\n    cols.forEach(c=>{\n      const opt = document.createElement('option');\n      opt.value = c.name;\n      opt.textContent = c.name;\n      relSourceColumnSelect.appendChild(opt);\n    });\n  }\n  function updateRelTargetColumns() {\n    const tname = relTargetTableSelect.value;\n    relTargetColumnSelect.innerHTML = '';\n    if(!tname || !state.tables[tname]) return;\n    const cols = state.tables[tname].columns;\n    cols.forEach(c=>{\n      const opt = document.createElement('option');\n      opt.value = c.name;\n      opt.textContent = c.name;\n      relTargetColumnSelect.appendChild(opt);\n    });\n  }\n\n  relSourceTableSelect.addEventListener('change', updateRelSourceColumns);\n  relTargetTableSelect.addEventListener('change', updateRelTargetColumns);\n\n  // Add Relation FK by user\n  btnAddRelation.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    const srcTable = relSourceTableSelect.value;\n    const srcColumn = relSourceColumnSelect.value;\n    const tgtTable = relTargetTableSelect.value;\n    const tgtColumn = relTargetColumnSelect.value;\n    if(!srcTable || !srcColumn || !tgtTable || !tgtColumn) {\n      alert('Select source table, source column, target table, and target column.');\n      return;\n    }\n    // Validate source column exists and source column type matches target column type\n    const srcTblObj = state.tables[srcTable];\n    const tgtTblObj = state.tables[tgtTable];\n    if(!srcTblObj || !tgtTblObj) {\n      alert('Source or target table not found.');\n      return;\n    }\n    const srcColObj = srcTblObj.columns.find(c => c.name === srcColumn);\n    const tgtColObj = tgtTblObj.columns.find(c => c.name === tgtColumn);\n    if(!srcColObj || !tgtColObj) {\n      alert('Source or target column not found.');\n      return;\n    }\n    if(srcColObj.type !== 'fk') {\n      alert('Source column must be a foreign key type to add relation.');\n      return;\n    }\n    if(!srcColObj.fkTarget || srcColObj.fkTarget.table !== tgtTable || srcColObj.fkTarget.column !== tgtColumn) {\n      alert('FK target table and column mismatch with source column FK definition.');\n      return;\n    }\n    // Check if relation already exists\n    if(state.relations.some(r => r.sourceTable === srcTable && r.sourceColumn === srcColumn && r.targetTable === tgtTable && r.targetColumn === tgtColumn)) {\n      alert('This relation already exists.');\n      return;\n    }\n    // Add relation\n    state.relations.push({sourceTable: srcTable,sourceColumn: srcColumn,targetTable: tgtTable,targetColumn: tgtColumn});\n    updateRelationsSection();\n    updateStateView();\n  });\n\n  // Update relations table display\n  function updateRelationsSection() {\n    if(!currentTable) {\n      relationsSection.style.display = 'none';\n      return;\n    }\n    relationsSection.style.display = '';\n    relationsTableBody.innerHTML = '';\n    state.relations.forEach((rel,i)=>{\n      const tr = document.createElement('tr');\n      const tdSrc = document.createElement('td');\n      tdSrc.textContent = rel.sourceTable + '.' + rel.sourceColumn;\n      const tdTgt = document.createElement('td');\n      tdTgt.textContent = rel.targetTable + '.' + rel.targetColumn;\n      const tdActions = document.createElement('td');\n      const btnDel = document.createElement('button');\n      btnDel.textContent = 'Remove';\n      btnDel.onclick = () => {\n        if(confirm('Remove this relation?')) {\n          state.relations.splice(i,1);\n          updateRelationsSection();\n          updateStateView();\n        }\n      };\n      tdActions.appendChild(btnDel);\n\n      tr.appendChild(tdSrc);\n      tr.appendChild(tdTgt);\n      tr.appendChild(tdActions);\n      relationsTableBody.appendChild(tr);\n    });\n  }\n\n  // QUERY SECTION\n  // Simple query engine: support SELECT columns FROM tables WHERE condition (AND only, =, !=, >, <, >=, <=)\n  // Also supports natural join on FK relations between tables\n  // SELECT with comma separated columns (qualified or unqualified)\n  // WHERE conditions separated by AND, each condition: [table.]column operator value (string/int)\n  // Result: table with selected columns or error messages\n\n  btnRunQuery.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    const tablesInput = querySelectTablesInput.value.trim();\n    const columnsInput = queryColumnsInput.value.trim();\n    const whereInput = queryWhereInput.value.trim();\n\n    if(!tablesInput) {\n      alert('Please enter table names.');\n      return;\n    }\n    if(!columnsInput) {\n      alert('Please enter columns to select.');\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Parse tables list\n    const tableNames = tablesInput.split(',').map(s => s.trim()).filter(s => s.length > 0);\n    // Validate tables exist\n    for(const tname of tableNames) {\n      if(!state.tables[tname]) {\n        alert(`Table \"${tname}\" does not exist.`);\n        return;\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Build combined dataset from tables with joins on FK relations (only natural joins using FK defined in relations)\n    // We do inner joins (only rows matching on the relation)\n    // Algorithm:\n    // Start with first table rows (array of objects keyed by table.column)\n    // For each other table:\n    // - Find relations between included tables (any relation between current combined tables and this table)\n    // - Join on those relations\n    // If no relation found joining to existing combined dataset, perform CROSS JOIN (all pairs)\n\n    // Construct datasets keyed by table.column\n    // row keys are qualified by table.column\n    // e.g. Employees.Name, Departments.Name\n\n    function qualifyRow(tableName, row) {\n      const res = {};\n      for(const col of Object.keys(row)) {\n        res[tableName + '.' + col] = row[col];\n      }\n      return res;\n    }\n\n    // Initial dataset is table1 rows qualified\n    let combinedRows = state.tables[tableNames[0]].rows.map(r => qualifyRow(tableNames[0], r));\n\n    for(let i=1; i < tableNames.length; i++) {\n      const newTable = tableNames[i];\n      const newRowsQualified = state.tables[newTable].rows.map(r => qualifyRow(newTable, r));\n      // Find relations connecting any table in combined set and newTable\n      // Relations can connect sourceTable to targetTable or vice versa (use both directions)\n      const connectedRelations = state.relations.filter(r => \n        (tableNames.includes(r.sourceTable) && r.targetTable === newTable) ||\n        (tableNames.includes(r.targetTable) && r.sourceTable === newTable)\n      );\n\n      if(connectedRelations.length === 0) {\n        // No relation: CROSS JOIN (can be very large)\n        const crossJoined = [];\n        for(const r1 of combinedRows) {\n          for(const r2 of newRowsQualified) {\n            crossJoined.push(Object.assign({}, r1, r2));\n          }\n        }\n        combinedRows = crossJoined;\n      } else {\n        // Inner join on all matched relations\n        let joinResult = [];\n        for(const r1 of combinedRows) {\n          for(const r2 of newRowsQualified) {\n            // Check all connected relations for this pair\n            let allMatch = true;\n            for(const rel of connectedRelations) {\n              let srcVal, tgtVal;\n              if(rel.sourceTable === newTable) {\n                // newTable is source\n                srcVal = r2[rel.sourceTable + '.' + rel.sourceColumn];\n                tgtVal = r1[rel.targetTable + '.' + rel.targetColumn];\n              } else {\n                // newTable is target\n                srcVal = r1[rel.sourceTable + '.' + rel.sourceColumn];\n                tgtVal = r2[rel.targetTable + '.' + rel.targetColumn];\n              }\n              if(srcVal !== tgtVal) {\n                allMatch = false;\n                break;\n              }\n            }\n            if(allMatch) {\n              joinResult.push(Object.assign({}, r1, r2));\n            }\n          }\n        }\n        combinedRows = joinResult;\n      }\n    }\n\n    // If no rows after join, clear result\n    if(combinedRows.length === 0) {\n      queryResultThead.innerHTML = '';\n      queryResultTbody.innerHTML = '';\n      alert('No results found for the query (empty result set).');\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Parse columns input\n    // columnsInput: comma separated selected columns, can be table.col or just col (should resolve uniquely)\n    const selectedColsRaw = columnsInput.split(',').map(s => s.trim()).filter(s => s.length>0);\n    const selectedCols = [];\n    for(const colRaw of selectedColsRaw) {\n      if(colRaw.includes('.')) {\n        // qualified\n        selectedCols.push(colRaw);\n      } else {\n        // unqualified - search tables for column\n        let foundTables = [];\n        for(const tname of tableNames) {\n          const t = state.tables[tname];\n          if(t.columns.some(c => c.name === colRaw)) {\n            foundTables.push(tname);\n          }\n        }\n        if(foundTables.length === 0) {\n          alert(`Column \"${colRaw}\" not found in any selected table.`);\n          return;\n        }\n        if(foundTables.length > 1) {\n          alert(`Ambiguous column \"${colRaw}\" found in multiple tables: ${foundTables.join(', ')}. Please qualify with table name.`);\n          return;\n        }\n        selectedCols.push(foundTables[0] + '.' + colRaw);\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Parse WHERE clause\n    // Simple support for AND separated conditions only, condition of form: [table.]column operator value\n    // Operators supported: = != > < >= <=\n    // Values: strings (single ' or double \" quotes) or numbers or bare words (treated as strings)\n    // e.g. Employees.Age > 25 AND Departments.Name = 'HR'\n\n    function parseWhere(whereStr) {\n      if(!whereStr) return [];\n      // Split by AND (ignore case)\n      const parts = whereStr.split(/AND/i).map(s => s.trim()).filter(s => s.length > 0);\n      const conds = [];\n      for(const part of parts) {\n        // Match pattern: [table.]column operator value\n        // operators regex: >=, <=, !=, =, >, <\n        // Use regex with capture groups\n        const m = part.match(/^(([a-zA-Z_]\\w*)\\.)?([a-zA-Z_]\\w*)\\s*(>=|<=|!=|=|>|<)\\s*(.+)$/);\n        if(!m) {\n          alert(`Invalid condition in WHERE clause: \"${part}\"`);\n          return null;\n        }\n        let [, , tbl, col, op, valRaw] = m;\n        if(!tbl) {\n          // unqualified column - resolve uniquely\n          let foundTables = [];\n          for(const tname of tableNames) {\n            const t = state.tables[tname];\n            if(t.columns.some(c => c.name === col)) {\n              foundTables.push(tname);\n            }\n          }\n          if(foundTables.length === 0) {\n            alert(`Column \"${col}\" not found in the query tables.`);\n            return null;\n          }\n          if(foundTables.length > 1) {\n            alert(`Ambiguous column \"${col}\" found in multiple tables in WHERE clause. Please qualify it.`);\n            return null;\n          }\n          tbl = foundTables[0];\n        }\n        // Parse valRaw - handle quoted strings or number or unquoted string\n        valRaw = valRaw.trim();\n        let val = valRaw;\n        if((valRaw.startsWith(\"'\") && valRaw.endsWith(\"'\")) || (valRaw.startsWith('\"') && valRaw.endsWith('\"'))) {\n          val = valRaw.slice(1,-1);\n        } else if(!isNaN(Number(valRaw))) {\n          val = Number(valRaw);\n        } else {\n          val = valRaw; // bare word string\n        }\n        conds.push({table: tbl, column: col, operator: op, value: val});\n      }\n      return conds;\n    }\n\n    const conditions = parseWhere(whereInput);\n    if(conditions === null) return;\n\n    // Evaluate conditions on combinedRows\n    function evalCondition(r, c) {\n      const key = c.table + '.' + c.column;\n      const val = r[key];\n      const condVal = c.value;\n      switch(c.operator) {\n        case '=': return val == condVal;\n        case '!=': return val != condVal;\n        case '>': return val > condVal;\n        case '<': return val < condVal;\n        case '>=': return val >= condVal;\n        case '<=': return val <= condVal;\n      }\n      return false;\n    }\n\n    const filteredRows = combinedRows.filter(r => {\n      for(const c of conditions) {\n        if(!evalCondition(r,c)) return false;\n      }\n      return true;\n    });\n\n    if(filteredRows.length === 0) {\n      queryResultThead.innerHTML = '';\n      queryResultTbody.innerHTML = '';\n      alert('No results found after applying WHERE conditions.');\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Display results table\n    queryResultThead.innerHTML = '';\n    queryResultTbody.innerHTML = '';\n\n    // Header row\n    const trHead = document.createElement('tr');\n    selectedCols.forEach(cn => {\n      const th = document.createElement('th');\n      th.textContent = cn;\n      trHead.appendChild(th);\n    });\n    queryResultThead.appendChild(trHead);\n    // Rows\n    filteredRows.forEach(r => {\n      const tr = document.createElement('tr');\n      selectedCols.forEach(cn => {\n        const td = document.createElement('td');\n        let val = r[cn];\n        if(val === undefined || val === null) val = '';\n        td.textContent = String(val);\n        tr.appendChild(td);\n      });\n      queryResultTbody.appendChild(tr);\n    });\n\n  });\n\n  // Initial update\n  updateTablesDropdowns();\n  updateStateView();\n\n  // Prepare FK select initial display\n  newColumnTypeSelect.dispatchEvent(new Event('change'));\n\n})();\n</script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
